# LuminoLearn — Cursor Instructions
# Drop this file as `.cursorrules` in the project root.
# Cursor reads it automatically on every prompt.

## Project Overview

LuminoLearn is a 3-role learning platform for students aged 9-17.
Built for boutique online tutoring with small group classes.

Stack:
- Next.js 14 (App Router) + TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui components
- Supabase (Postgres + Auth + Storage + Realtime)
- Stripe (payments + customer portal)
- Twilio (SMS notifications)
- Resend (email notifications)
- Zoom or Google Meet (live classes, embedded)

---

## Three User Roles

**Student account**
- Sees only enrolled courses (Number Ninjas, Word Wizards, Code Explorers)
- Joins live class via embedded video link
- Submits homework via file upload (Word, PDF, image) or Google Docs URL
- Views personal schedule and progress chart
- Receives SMS and email for new assignments and feedback

**Parent account** (linked to student, passcode-gated)
- Same login as student, separate passcode (4-6 digit) to switch view
- Read-only progress reports per course
- Full payment history with downloadable Stripe receipts
- Manages SMS notification preferences
- Cannot edit homework or join classes

**Teacher account**
- Sees roster of all assigned students
- Creates lesson plans with structured chapters
- Assigns homework with due dates, attachment requirements
- Reviews submitted work, leaves written or audio feedback
- Sees and edits the master schedule

---

## Lumino Curriculum Structure

**Stages (placement by ability, not grade):**
- Foundations (9-11)
- Growth (12-14)
- Mastery (15-17)

**Subjects:**
- Number Ninjas → Mathematics
- Word Wizards → Language & Literacy
- Code Explorers → Computer Science (includes AI ethics from age 12)

**Learning Journey:**
1. Discovery call (free, 30 min)
2. LuminoStart™ (4-week placement assessment)
3. LuminoCore™ (12-week certified cycle)
4. LuminoPath™ (3-12 month bundles)

---

## Architecture Rules

### Routing (Next.js App Router)
- All routes are in `app/` directory
- Each role has its own folder: `app/student/`, `app/parent/`, `app/teacher/`
- Shared layouts in `app/(auth)/` for login flows
- Never put role-specific logic in components — pass props from page level

### State
- Use Supabase Realtime for live notifications
- Use React Server Components by default
- Client components only when interaction is required (`'use client'` directive)
- Never use localStorage for sensitive data — use Supabase session

### Data
- All site content lives in Supabase tables
- Course content, lesson structures, and student data — never hard-coded
- Use Supabase RLS (Row Level Security) policies for all tables
- Students can only read their own enrollments
- Parents can read their linked student's data
- Teachers can read all assigned students

---

## Database Schema

```
profiles
  id, role (student/parent/teacher), full_name, email, phone, avatar_url, created_at

family_links
  parent_id, student_id, passcode_hash, created_at

courses
  id, name (number_ninjas/word_wizards/code_explorers), stage (foundations/growth/mastery)

lessons
  id, course_id, week, title, chapters (jsonb), zoom_link

enrollments
  id, student_id, course_id, teacher_id, cycle (start/core/path), week_progress, status

homework
  id, lesson_id, instructions, due_date, attachment_types (jsonb array), max_score

submissions
  id, homework_id, student_id, file_url, google_doc_url, submitted_at, score, feedback, audio_feedback_url

assessments
  id, student_id, type (lumino_start/3_week/3_month), score, baseline_score, date

payments
  id, parent_id, student_id, amount_cents, currency, stripe_payment_id, status, invoice_url, paid_at, due_date

notifications
  id, user_id, type, channel (in_app/email/sms), message, link, read_at, sent_at

notification_prefs
  user_id, sms_homework, sms_class, sms_payment, sms_feedback, email_*, phone_verified, opted_in_at

sms_log
  id, user_id, trigger_event, message_body, twilio_sid, status, sent_at

schedule_slots
  id, course_id, teacher_id, day_of_week, start_time, end_time, recurring
```

