## Styling Rules

### Brand Tokens
Defined in `tailwind.config.ts` and `app/globals.css`:

```
Colors:
  lumino-purple-50  #EEEDFE  (Math/Number Ninjas light)
  lumino-purple-600 #534AB7  (Math primary)
  lumino-purple-900 #26215C  (Math text on light)

  lumino-amber-50   #FAEEDA  (Language/Word Wizards light)
  lumino-amber-600  #BA7517  (Language primary)
  lumino-amber-900  #412402

  lumino-blue-50    #E6F1FB  (CS/Code Explorers light)
  lumino-blue-600   #185FA5  (CS primary)
  lumino-blue-900   #042C53

  lumino-teal-600   #1D9E75  (success/completion)
  lumino-coral-600  #993C1D  (alerts/urgent)

Fonts:
  --font-display: Inter (headings, UI)
  --font-body:    Inter (body, labels)
  --font-mono:    JetBrains Mono (code blocks in CS lessons)
```

### Always use Tailwind utility classes — never inline styles
```tsx
// CORRECT
<div className="bg-lumino-purple-50 text-lumino-purple-900 p-4 rounded-lg">

// WRONG
<div style={{ background: '#EEEDFE', color: '#26215C', padding: 16 }}>
```

### Always use shadcn/ui components for forms, dialogs, buttons
```bash
npx shadcn-ui@latest add button card dialog input form select badge
```

### Typography scale
- h1 = text-2xl font-medium
- h2 = text-lg font-medium
- h3 = text-base font-medium
- body = text-sm
- meta = text-xs text-muted-foreground

### Accessibility (AAA standards)
- All interactive elements need focus-visible ring
- Contrast ratios must meet WCAG AA minimum
- Every icon-only button needs `aria-label`
- Forms use shadcn `<Form>` with proper field labels

---

## Component Guidelines

### CourseCard
Used on student dashboard. Receives the course object and renders the icon, title, lesson progress, and "Join class" CTA. Branded by course type (Math/Language/CS).

### HomeworkRow
List item for homework assignments. Shows status pill (Due soon / In progress / Submitted), course, due date, action button.

### CycleProgressStrip
Shows the 4-step LuminoLearn journey: Discovery → LuminoStart → LuminoCore → LuminoPath. Highlights current step.

### ProgressChart
Bar chart showing assessment scores from LuminoStart baseline through current. Uses recharts library.

### FileUploadField
Homework submission widget. Accepts .docx, .pdf, .png, .jpg. Also has "Paste Google Docs URL" alternative input. Uploads to Supabase Storage.

### SmsPreferences
Toggle panel for SMS opt-in. Separate switches for homework, class reminders, payment alerts, feedback. Includes CASL-compliant consent text.

---

## SMS Notifications (Twilio)

All SMS sent via Twilio. Trigger events:

| Event | Recipient | Trigger location |
|---|---|---|
| Homework assigned | Student + Parent | When teacher creates row in `homework` table |
| Homework submitted | Parent + Teacher | When student creates row in `submissions` |
| Feedback posted | Student + Parent | When teacher updates `submissions.feedback` |
| Payment reminder (7 days) | Parent | Cron job: 7 days before `payments.due_date` |
| Payment overdue | Parent | Cron job: 1 day after `payments.due_date` if status != paid |
| Class starting (30 min) | Student | Cron job based on `schedule_slots` |
| 3-month evaluation | Parent + Student | Cron job: 90 days after last `assessments` of type `3_month` |

All SMS go through `lib/sms.ts` helper that:
1. Checks `notification_prefs` for user's opt-in
2. Sends via Twilio Programmable SMS API
3. Logs result to `sms_log`
4. Honours STOP keyword automatically (Twilio handles)

CASL compliance:
- Explicit opt-in checkbox during signup (unchecked by default)
- Confirmation SMS on first opt-in
- "Reply STOP to opt out" appended to every message
- Unsubscribe toggle in Settings always available

